      "audio_duration_seconds": 0.0,
      "transcript": "I am currently at the North Orchard checking the apple trees. It looks like we have a minor aphid infestation starting on the lower branches of Row 12. I'd like to schedule a spraying for tomorrow morning, preferably before 10AM, using organic pesticides from the shed. Also a reminder for the maintenance team that tractor number four has a slight hydraulic leak in the left arm. We need to get this fixed before the harvest starts next Monday. Please order a new seal jet if we don't have one in stock. Also, observation from the South Field, soil moisture levels are looking great after the rain last night, about 75%. Let's disable the automatic irrigation for the next forty eight hours to save on water usage.",
